<subSubSection id="58BAFFD3EB687BA679180E02D6FACF15" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="4DB3ACC253104F81AE9D0D57F6688C97" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F55A5669DAA397FE0414814ECAA0A2B4" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="AE5C9428461216499121D6B0727E96B6" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">
<emphasis id="FA1D4811A9865C3B23AC278C1445A33F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the Spanish provinces of Cuenca and Teruel. While it is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="6F2550948CB1D2846BC8D9FA326A82F1" authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis id="4E91112CA2DF93CFCD60DB1729E5DCF5" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from south-eastern and southern-central France, the placement of this taxon as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="B7E305B9AF3D477ED93E2C4F55D6270A" authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">
<emphasis id="375F3252DAC0D3673CCC8E81D9BA7B8B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="54CACC444871D2AA5AA2C1A577121E0A" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 98), which he reinstated as a valid subspecies, is inconsistent with the geographical distribution, its 
<normalizedToken id="F73F803D6A853C24FBB8DBA59F05DA42" originalValue="‘griseoid’">'griseoid'</normalizedToken>
phenotype and the presence of a strong abdominal cingulum. As a consequence, 
<taxonomicName id="B676920C04B98DE5762AE4C34E7A82DE" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">
<emphasis id="BC75682778437AE7ACEC683EAA644BBD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reinstated (
<emphasis id="CAFCB812963FCC1BAF2B878DB43103EC" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">stat. rev.</emphasis>
) as a valid subspecies (
<bibRefCitation id="62FF3533D476FD70E878172B1FA4538B" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
: 130). It should be noted that 
<taxonomicName id="53FA6666CFDA57EA2ADCAB9236D1B12D" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Hofmann &amp; Tarmann &amp; Tremewan" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">
<emphasis id="0A15ED96363D36D2448E47CA8647BBCC" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="128">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a griseoid phenotype and a strong abdominal cingulum, but the two taxa are geographically separated by a large lowland area that includes the River Ebro.
</paragraph>
